# Omni File System (OFS)

## Overview
The Omni File System (OFS) is a custom filesystem implemented in C++ that allows managing files, directories, users, and metadata inside a single `.omni` container file. It supports secure user authentication, file operations, directory operations, permissions, and filesystem statistics.

---

## Features
- File operations: create, read, edit, delete, truncate, rename, check existence
- Directory operations: create, list, delete, check existence
- Metadata retrieval and permission management
- User management: add, remove, list users
- Filesystem statistics: usage, free space, fragmentation
- Secure admin and user authentication

---

## Compilation

To compile the project, run:


g++ -std=c++17 -I./source/include -I./source/data_structures source/core/*.cpp -o compiled/main
Running
After compiling, run the executable:

./compiled/main
Usage
User Authentication
Login:
SessionInfo* session;
user_login(instance, "admin", "admin_password", &session);
Logout:
user_logout(session);
File Operations
file_create(session, "/example.txt");
char* buffer;
size_t size;
file_read(session, "/example.txt", &buffer, &size);
file_edit(session, "/example.txt", data, size, index);
file_delete(session, "/example.txt");
file_truncate(session, "/example.txt", new_size);
file_rename(session, "/old.txt", "/new.txt");
file_exists(session, "/example.txt");
free_buffer(buffer);
Directory Operations
dir_create(session, "/mydir");
FileEntry* entries;
int count;
dir_list(session, "/mydir", &entries, &count);
dir_delete(session, "/mydir");
dir_exists(session, "/mydir");
Metadata and Permissions
FileMetadata meta;
get_metadata(session, "/example.txt", &meta);
set_permissions(session, "/example.txt", 0755);
FSStats stats;
get_stats(session, &stats);
Admin Operations
user_add(instance, "newuser", "password", role);
user_remove(instance, "username");
UserEntry* users;
int count;
user_list(instance, &users, &count);
Admin operations use the filesystem instance directly and do not require an active session.
Shutdown
Always cleanly shut down the filesystem to persist changes:
fs_shutdown(instance);


